  "governance_notes": "All children are leaf nodes. ParseInput and TrackOrder are pure functions with no data store mutations. PlaceOrder and CancelOrder are atomic operations that require read_write access to orders, inventory, and payments data stores. Global vars for each child are subsets of parent's available data stores. Data operations cover all parent data needs: orders (read_write for place/cancel, read for track), inventory (read_write for place/cancel), payments (read_write for place/cancel)."
